# Agent verbs — SAVE · WORK · EDIT ALLOWED (000)

**Law:** `brain-os/law/enforcement/AGENT_VERBS_SAVE_WORK_EDIT_LOCKED_v1.md`  
**On conflict:** [skill-007-ecosystem-conflict-resolution](../skills/skill-007-ecosystem-conflict-resolution/SKILL.md) · [ecosystem-rule-conflict-resolution.mdc](ecosystem-rule-conflict-resolution.mdc) · R-010

## SAVE / LOCK / FILE (registry-first)

**ASF never needs to provide exact save paths when registry routing can resolve the destination.**

- First resolve path from `data/agent-filing-registry-v1.json`
- Machine gate:

```bash
python3 scripts/agent_filing_registry_gate_v1.py resolve --agent <id> --intent "<founder message>" --json
```

- If `ok:true` → use resolved `path`, then run pre-write / cross-lane guard before writing.
- If `ok:false REGISTRY_NO_MATCH` or `REGISTRY_AMBIGUOUS` → ask ASF to choose category/scope, **not exact path**.
- Report proof as: `route_id` + resolved path.
- Do not create ad hoc paths outside the registry.

## WORK (SourceA Worker / Product build)

**Bound INBOX / sa-* / product code — execute at full speed. No extra ASK inside scope.**

## EDIT ALLOWED (cross-desk)

`EDIT ALLOWED: <path>` + `ACTION:` in same founder message — else **REFUSE**.

## Guard (research / cross-lane only — Worker scoped paths pass)

```bash
python3 scripts/cross_lane_edit_guard_v1.py check --agent <id> --path "<target>" --json
```

Inspect `ok` — do not write if `false` and you are not on WORK scope.
